main event: A pilot reported seeing an object with 15 circular swirls of light appear on film and then go off the film in 10 seconds at Point Mugu, California on March 23, 1957.
interesting points: The object was irregular in shape and moved rapidly, with no sound or trail.
The pilot's report was forwarded to the Navy and was unavailable for analysis.
No conclusions could be made about the object.
The sighting was captured on a 35mm Mitchell high-speed camera.
sighted object: an object with 15 circular swirls of light
photographs: yes, the object was captured on film
